{
  "stem": "9899.3",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Although I didn't know much about it, and my mother didn't know what to do when Easter came or the other holidays that were observed, we made do, and she pushed us on, cared for us, and gave us the best of whatever was available at that time, which was very little.",
      "word_count": 52
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "We had added to our staple of bread, black bread and water, we have a little bit of milk and a little bit-- we had a cow, so we had a little bit of milk.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "The woman who cared for us while my mother was going from town to town selling her goods would feed us, would take care of us, in a way, and would tell me also, if you don't eat, the Jew is going to get you.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "So I grew up fearing the Jews, thinking they were some kind of monsters, inhuman, and that this was the way life was.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And in this fear, our time of a year and a half finished in Buczacz.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And we-- there were rumors that the Russians were coming, and the Germans were retreated.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Retreating.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "At that time, Buczacz, Lwow, and all the surrounding cities were Judenfrei, which is free of Jews.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "There were no more Jews to be found in any of that area.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They had all been either killed or deported to the larger camps for the extermination.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They were all put into ovens.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They were all killed.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "From our family, we did not know anything.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But one day, the Germans came in and said, you all have to leave because the Russians are coming, and we are burning the village down.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "You may not stay here any longer.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
